# =============================================================================
# VSW Slack Intake Service — environment template
# Copy to `.env` and fill in real values. NEVER commit the real .env.
# All secrets live only here (local) and in Railway variables in production.
# =============================================================================

# --- Runtime -----------------------------------------------------------------
PORT=8080
TZ=America/Vancouver
NODE_ENV=development
LOG_LEVEL=info

# --- Slack app (NEW — a real bot, not the existing incoming webhook) ---------
# Create at api.slack.com/apps. Socket Mode is the recommended transport (no
# public events endpoint to expose). Bot scopes: chat:write, files:read,
# app_mentions:read. Event subscriptions: app_mention (+ optional file_shared).
SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-...            # Bot User OAuth Token
SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET=...            # Basic Information → App Credentials
SLACK_APP_TOKEN=xapp-...            # App-Level Token, scope connections:write (Socket Mode only)
SLACK_ADMIN_USER_ID=...             # Your Slack user ID (e.g. U08TKLJH4QL) — only this user can react :wastebasket: to delete a bot message
SLACK_CHANNEL_ID=C0BEUTEDAF4        # #tej-bots — where the nightly promotion sweep (PRD §10.2) posts its summary

# --- Existing n8n webhook (URL intake path forwards here; unchanged engine) --
# The service does NOT scrape URLs itself — it POSTs {urls:[...],note} here and
# n8n runs Firecrawl/Stagehand → extract → dedup → write → its own Slack notice.
N8N_SCRAPE_URL_WEBHOOK=https://primary-production-9c98.up.railway.app/webhook/vsw/scrape-url

# --- Google Sheets (data-staging is written directly by this service) --------
# Recommended: a Google service account with edit access to the sheet.
# Local dev: point at the JSON key file (kept in ./secrets/, gitignored).
GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=./secrets/service-account.json
# Railway (or anywhere without a local filesystem for the key file): paste the
# service account's ENTIRE JSON key as one line here instead — takes priority
# over GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS when set. Get the raw JSON from the same
# service-account.json file; keep it as valid single-line JSON when pasting
# into Railway's variable editor.
# GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON={"type":"service_account","project_id":"...", ...}
GOOGLE_SHEETS_SPREADSHEET_ID=1GZ0dvzz_ODdJ3Cd9jKfmPZtOjI-_w5f-LEDvT-ecDaQ
STAGING_TAB_NAME=data-staging
STAGING_TAB_GID=186943567
MASTER_TAB_NAME=master-prospects
MASTER_HEADER_ROW=2
MASTER_TAB_GID=                     # gid of the master-prospects tab — used in the promotion summary's Sheet link
# --- OR OAuth (if you prefer the client ID/secret you mentioned over a SA) ---
# GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=...
# GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=...
# GOOGLE_OAUTH_REFRESH_TOKEN=...

# --- Gemini (VISION: reads sponsor-logo screenshots → org names) -------------
# Decision 2026-07-03: Google Gemini is the vision provider for the image path.
# Confirm the current GA model id at build time (e.g. gemini-2.5-pro for
# accuracy, gemini-2.5-flash for cost). Optional Google Search grounding can
# resolve a logo → real company + website in one call (see AGENTS.md §Vision).
GEMINI_API_KEY=...
GEMINI_VISION_MODEL=gemini-2.5-pro

# --- Anthropic (CLASSIFICATION: Category/Sector/Why Them for CSV+image rows) -
# Kept as classification provider so this service's rows match the Category
# enum/style that n8n writes for URL rows. Rotate the key that sat in the
# deploy-kit doc (see Execution Log 2026-07-03).
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=...
ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-5

# --- Promotion Agent (tool-using loop, PRD §11 / PLAN Stage 7) -----------------
# Separate model from ANTHROPIC_MODEL above (which is the intake-classification
# model). The Promotion Agent's reasoning loop uses Sonnet, not Opus — Tej's
# explicit preference (this is judgment + tool orchestration, not the kind of
# task that needs the slowest/priciest model).
PROMOTION_AGENT_MODEL=claude-sonnet-5

# --- Firecrawl (Promotion Agent's own research tools, PRD §11 / AGENTS.md #5) -
# Not used by the intake paths (n8n still owns URL scraping — golden rule #5).
# Required for the Promotion Agent's firecrawl_search/firecrawl_scrape tools —
# it's the one deliberate, scoped exception, so this key is required for that
# feature even though the rest of the service never touches the open web.
FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=fc-...

# --- Notion (Promotion Agent run log — PRD §11.6 / PLAN Stage 7D) -----------
# Create an internal integration at notion.so/my-integrations, share it with
# the target page, then create a database under that page (or reuse the one
# already created 2026-07-04: "Promotion Agent — Run Log", under "VSW Future
# Planning"). One database ROW (= one Notion page) gets created per Promotion
# Agent run — never a running/shared log. Row properties: Run (title), Date,
# Trigger (on-demand/nightly), Status (success/partial/failed), Added, Merged,
# Skipped - Review, Skipped - Source Type, Failed, Tokens spent, Firecrawl
# calls, Slack thread (url). Full prompt/tool-call/result trace + citations
# live in each row's page body.
NOTION_API_KEY=ntn_...
NOTION_PROMOTION_LOG_DATABASE_ID=...  # the database's ID (from its URL)

# --- #vsw-future-planning -> "Thread with Andrew" Notion mirror (2026-07-13) -
# Passively logs every message + thread reply in this Slack channel onto the
# Notion page, newest first — see src/threadLog/notionThreadLog.ts. Reuses
# NOTION_API_KEY above; that integration must also be shared with this
# specific Notion page (Notion integrations only see pages explicitly shared
# with them — sharing the Promotion Log database does NOT also grant this).
# Requires the `message.channels` Event Subscription + `channels:history`
# bot scope (reinstall the Slack app after adding), and the bot must be
# invited into #vsw-future-planning — see AGENTS.md §Setup.
VSW_FUTURE_PLANNING_CHANNEL_ID=C0B5Q81AV41
NOTION_THREAD_LOG_PAGE_ID=38e6b6f2b95b8068b183c49d924e5906

# --- Railway persistent Volume (production only) -----------------------------
# Railway's default filesystem is wiped on every redeploy/restart. Mount a
# Volume (e.g. at /data) and point these two at it so the pending-question
# queue and the Source Type decision cache survive across deploys — leave
# both unset locally (defaults live under this repo's own state/ and
# src/promote/ instead). A fresh Volume with no source-type-cache.json yet
# gets seeded from the committed one automatically (sourceTypeCache.ts).
# PENDING_QUESTIONS_PATH_OVERRIDE=/data/pending-questions.json
# SOURCE_TYPE_CACHE_PATH_OVERRIDE=/data/source-type-cache.json
# THREAD_LOG_STATE_PATH_OVERRIDE=/data/thread-log.json
# ^ Without this on Railway, a redeploy loses the "which reply nests under
# which message" mapping. Not data loss — recordSlackMessage() falls back to
# logging an orphaned reply as its own top-level entry — just less tidy.

# --- Service auth (optional, if you also expose an HTTP endpoint) ------------
# INTAKE_API_KEY=...
